🚀 What is V8?
V8 = JavaScript Engine created by Google
It is the program that runs JavaScript code.
👉 Without V8, JavaScript cannot run.
So:
Your JS code → V8 → Machine code → CPU executes
🧠 Why V8 Exists
Computers understand only:
Binary (0 and 1)

But you write:
let x = 5;

So something must translate JS → machine language.
👉 That translator = V8 engine
🌍 Where V8 is Used

V8 runs JavaScript in:
Google Chrome
Microsoft Edge (Chromium)
Node.js
Deno
Many servers

So when you run:
node app.js
👉 Node uses V8 internally.

